Cactus Code Thorn ScalarInit
Author(s)    : Helvi Witek, Giuseppe Ficarra
Maintainer(s): Helvi Witek, Giuseppe Ficarra
Licence      : GPLv2+
--------------------------------------------------------------------------

1. Purpose
===========
The thorn ScalarInit provides initial data for a (massive), complex scalar field as outlined in Sec. IIC of Witek et al '12.
Current choices include
- single mode Gaussian
  $phi=0$, $Kphi_{lm} =  Y_{lm} (\theta,\varphi) \exp\left[-\frac{(r-r_0)^2}{w^2} \right]$
  where $Y_{lm}$ are spherical harmonics, $r_{0}$ the location of the center of the Gaussian and $w$ its width.
- Gaussian containing a superposition of modes
- (quasi-) boundstates for massive fields

2. Applications
================
- evolution of massive scalar fields in the background of rotating black holes (see Witek et al '12)
- study scalar perturbations in time domain in GR and beyond (see Witek et al '12; Benkel et al '16; Witek et al '18)


3. References 
==============
- Witek et al, https://arxiv.org/abs/1212.0551
- for bound-states see Sam Dolan, https://arxiv.org/abs/0705.2880

